Preparation Time : 10 mins
Baking Time : 18 to 20 mins
Makes : 12 muffins

Ingredients:

All Purpose Flour / Maida - 1 1/4 cup / 150 grams
Cornflour - 3 tblspn
Cocoa Powder - 1/4 cup / 30 grams
Baking Powder - 1 tsp
Baking Soda - 1/2 tsp
Sugar - 3/4 cup / 150 grams
Yogurt / Curd - 1 cup / 240 ml
Oil - 1/2 cup / 120 ml
Vanilla Essence - 1 tsp
Tutti frutti - 1/2 cup 

(My 1 cup measures 240 ml)

Method:

Preheat oven to 180 degree C. Line 12 cup muffin pan with cupcake wrappers. Set aside.

Take all purpose flour, cornflour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and mix well. Set aside.

Take few spoons from this mix and toss with tutti fruiti so the tutti fruity dont sink to the bottom of muffins.

Now take yogurt, sugar, oil, vanilla in a bowl and mix well till sugar melts.

Now add the flour mix and tutti fruity mix in this and fold gently.

Use a icecream scoop to fill cupcake wrappers. Top with more tutti fruity if needed.

Bake for 18 to 20 mins.

Remove it and cool it down. 

Serve.